place.name: WESTFIELD
place.gazetteerText: WESTFIELD, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; ¾ mile W of Yaxham r. station, and 12¼ S by E of East Dereham. Post town, Dereham. Acres, 569. Real property, £1,215. Pop., 124. Houses, 31. The manor belongs to Mrs. Grigson. The living is a rectory, annexed to Whinbergh. The church is early English. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
